<TITLE> Ports cautioned over Bay depression </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  The weather office has asked Cox's Bazar, Mongla and Chittagong sea ports to hoist local cautionary signal number 3 as a clear depression formed over the Bay of Bengal on Friday. Under the impact of the depression the sky remained cloudy in most of the country including Dhaka since morning. The on-duty meteorologist at the weather office, Abdul Mannan, said some places were experiencing drizzle. "The depression that formed over west-middle Bay of Bengal Thursday turned into a clear depression Friday morning. "It was staying on the west middle and adjoining northwest Bay of Bengal by 12 noon," Mannan said. The met office asked all fishing boats and trawlers staying on the Bay of Bengal to stay near the coast and move cautiously until otherwise told. bd
